quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  106,1,"For the accustomed security of the Quraysh[1] -","[1] i.e., the honor and reputation Allāh had given them as guardians of the Holy Kaʿbah, which allowed them to travel without fear of being harmed."
  106,2,"Their accustomed security [in] the caravan of winter and summer[1] -","[1] i.e., the trading caravans that traveled south in winter and north in summer."
  106,3,"Let them worship the Lord of this House,[1]","[1] i.e., the Kaʿbah."
  106,4,"Who has fed them, [saving them] from hunger and made them safe, [saving them] from fear.",""
  107,1,"Have you seen the one who denies the Recompense?",""
  107,2,"For that is the one who drives away the orphan",""
  107,3,"And does not encourage the feeding of the poor.",""
  107,4,"So woe to those who pray",""
  107,5,"[But] who are heedless of their prayer[1] -","[1] i.e., the hypocrites who are unconcerned if they miss prayers when no one sees them."
  107,6,"Those who make show [of their deeds]",""
  107,7,"And withhold [simple] assistance.",""
  108,1,"Indeed, We have granted you, [O Muḥammad], al-Kawthar.",""
  108,2,"So pray to your Lord and offer sacrifice [to Him alone].",""
  108,3,"Indeed, your enemy is the one cut off.[1]","[1] From all good in this world and the Hereafter."
